<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-NCq50gx-NRNB6MC8ehm1AQ" name="measurement_assessment,_QQZNcAzwEd6ERc3uCTKYXQ" guid="-NCq50gx-NRNB6MC8ehm1AQ" changeDate="2009-04-28T12:01:49.312-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <purpose>&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To review the adherence to the measurement process as outlined in the Measurement Process Model&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To review the appropriateness of the various measures being captured.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To recommend changes to the process and to the measures being collected.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
  <impactOfNotHaving>If this artifact is not used, there is no formal record of the assessment and no roadmap for change.</impactOfNotHaving>
  <briefOutline>&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Assessment:&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Tool configuration and infrastructure&lt;/strong>: Investigation of the tools and whether they are producing&#xD;
        the anticipated automatic generation of the measures&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Measurement process:&lt;/strong> Evaluation of the measurement process, consisting of who, when, what and how&#xD;
        is reviewed to ensure optimal efficiencies&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Team usage model:&lt;/strong> Review of how the various team members are using the measures, which includes&#xD;
        all levels of the software development organization&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Recommendations&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This section gives a detailed recommendation on the changes that need to be made to the performance measurement system,&#xD;
    including all three aspects of the assessment.&#xD;
&lt;/p></briefOutline>
  <representationOptions>This information is normally captured in a word processing document, but the information could also be placed into a&#xD;
presentation format.</representationOptions>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
